[SN]TITLE[SN]
Liverpool given fine for fan fireworks in Dortmund game

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Liverpool have been fined 11,000 euros (£8,384) by Uefa after fans set off fireworks during their Europa League quarter-final tie against Dortmund.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
It comes a day after the Reds were handed a £43,577 fine for "illicit chants" and other misdemeanours against rivals Manchester United.
Liverpool lost in the final to Sevilla, with both sides being charged for crowd disturbances in that match.
The latter case will be dealt with by Uefa on 21 July.
